The game will eventually end with the player eventually hitting the edge of the screen or the snake (itself), leaving your terminal looking buggy afterwards. A fix is to wrap all your code into a function (e.g. def main(): ...) and then wrap the `main` function with curses.wrapper. For example:

def main():
    ....code...

if _name_ == '__main__':
    wrapper(main)﻿
